long_description:
Dum Dum® Original Pops (500 ct.) have been an American favorite lollipop since their creation in 1924. With 16 fun flavors plus the signature Mystery Flavor, these dum dum lollipops are perfect for kids of all ages—and grownups too! This Dum Dum Original Pops pack is the best way to grab a large amount of candy for kids' birthday parties, as Halloween goodies, school events or just to stock your home with sweet treats.

Try All 16 Original Dum Dum Flavors

From the fruity goodness of Blu Raspberry, Cherry, Orange, Sour Apple, Pineapple, Peach-Mango, Grape, Strawberry, Watermelon, Lemon-Lime and Fruit Punch to the tantalizingly sweetness of Root Beer, Cream Soda, Bubblegum, Butterscotch and Cotton Candy, Dum Dum original pops boast a jaw-dropping 16 total flavors. And don't forget to look for the Mystery Flavor in this 500-count bag of Dum Dum lollipops! Which flavor will you try next?

How Were Dum Dum Original Pops Invented?

Dum Dum lollipops were created by the Akron Candy Co. of Ohio, in 1924. I.C. Bahr, the sales manager of the company, named the candy on a stick because he felt it was an easy-to-say, memorable name. Now owned by Spangler Candy, Dum Dums and their original Dum Dum flavors are still manufactured in Ohio, where enthusiasts may take a factory tour.

How Else Can I Enjoy Dum Dum Original Pops?

Top cupcakes or monster-themed birthday cake with Dum Dum Original Pops and adhere edible eyes to look like colorful eyeballs. To celebrate springtime, create a Dum Dum lollipop centerpiece by sticking the pops into a ceramic vessel of fake grass and jelly beans to look like a garden of colorful, sugary delights.
